        </div>

        <div class="border-l-[3px] border-rose-500 pl-6 py-5 bg-rose-100 rounded-r">
          <p class="text-sm font-black text-rose-800 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">THE 4-MONTH BREAKDOWN</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed"><strong>Month 1:</strong> Shopify launch. Professional product photography uploaded (12 shots per product = 5x more sales - customers see quality). Ingredient list prominent ("Rosehip Oil - Vitamin C for brightening" = 4x more trust than buried descriptions). Shade finder quiz launched ("Find Your Perfect Glow" - 1,200 quiz completions, 34% conversion). Email capture added to quiz (67% provide email = 800 new leads). Month 1 sales: $12,400 (47% increase from $8,400). <strong>Month 2:</strong> Subscription refill option launched ("Subscribe & Save 15%" - receive every 4/6/8 weeks, cancel anytime). Month 2: 34 subscribers ($2,500/month recurring). Email automation added (welcome sequence: ingredient education, shade matching tips). Month 2 sales: $17,600. <strong>Month 3:</strong> Influencer UGC gallery launched (23 micro-influencers traded product for content). UGC drives 43% of traffic. Before/after photo gallery (12 customer results posted weekly). Month 3: 78 subscribers ($5,700/month recurring). Month 3 sales: $21,200. <strong>Month 4:</strong> Email list hits 12,000 (quiz captures 67% of 4,200 quiz takers). Email marketing drives 43% of sales. Subscribers 115 ($8,400/month recurring). Quiz completions: 4,200/month, 34% convert = 1,428 quiz-driven sales. Month 4 sales: $24,800 (195% increase from $8,400). Email response time: 3 hours â†’ 1 hour daily (shade finder quiz answers common questions automatically). Inventory never stocked out (Shopify batch tracking prevents stockouts - organic products have expiry dates, can't afford stockouts). The transformation: Ingredient transparency + shade personalization + subscription convenience = beauty brand customers trust and return to.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

