          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">Etsy-only sales: $8,400/month. Shopify launch: $24,800/month in 4 months (195% increase). Subscription revenue: $8,400/month (115 subscribers @ $73/month - was $0 before). Email list: 12,000 (quiz captures 67% of 4,200 quiz takers). Shade finder quiz: "Find Your Perfect Glow" 3-question quiz (skin type + tone + concerns) recommends products, 34% convert to purchase. Key features driving growth: Crystal-clear product photography (12 shots per product, 5x more sales - quality photos = quality perceived), ingredient list prominent (4x more trust - transparency builds confidence in clean beauty), subscription refill visible ("Subscribe & Save 15%" - 115 subscribers in 4 months, 73% repeat purchase rate vs. 34% on Etsy), before/after photos (real customer results with timestamps - social proof drives 43% of traffic), influencer gallery (UGC from 23 micro-influencers - 12K Instagram followers, UGC drives 43% of traffic). Build cost: $2,200 (Shopify $29/month + product photography $1,200 + quiz app $50/month + 25 hours brand time @ $30/hr). ROI: 195% sales increase, 1-month payback 11x. Shopify wins for beauty brands selling products: inventory management prevents stockouts (batch tracking, expiry dates for organic products), subscription support native (recurring billing built-in - 115 subscribers generating $8,400/month recurring), shade finder apps (quiz integration = 67% higher conversion). But monthly costs add up ($29 base + $50-200 in typical beauty apps + payment processing 2.9%). Only profitable after $2,500+ monthly sales.</p>
